==English==

====Pronunciation====
'''Do*de-ca-nese*'''
DOH-deh-kaah-neez

====Etymology====
Greek ''[[dodekanesos]]'', the twelve islands, from ''[[dodeka]]'', twelve, + ''[[nesos]]'', island.

===Proper noun===
'''Dodecanese'''
# An island chain consisting of twelve main islands including [[Rhodes]], its capital.

